Objectives:

  1. Apply buoyancy corrections to measurements made using an analytical balance.
  2. Propagate error across the steps of an analytical procedure. 
  3. Calculate and apply confidence intervals to measurements. 
  4. Use statistical tests to compare measurement means and standard deviations.
